  "body": "Question raised on [ethereum/solidity-dev gitter channel](https://gitter.im/ethereum/solidity-dev?at=5a8475644a6b0dd32bcf4642):\r\n\r\n> Would a contract starting with `0xfd` (`REVERT`) consume all gas allowance? Since there's nothing on the stack?..\r\n\r\n(And `REVERT` consumes two items from the stack.)\r\n\r\nFrom the yellowpaper (BYZANTIUM REVISION (6066b2d - 2018-01-19); section 8):\r\n\r\n> (...) if the **execution halts in an exceptional fashion** (i.e. due to an exhausted gas supply, **stack underflow**, invalid jump destination or invalid instruction), then **no gas is refunded to the caller** and the state is reverted to the point immediately prior to balance transfer (...).\r\n\r\nI tried searching for such a test case (query: [`\"code\" : \"0xfd\"`](https://github.com/ethereum/tests/search?utf8=%E2%9C%93&q=%22code%22+%3A+%220xfd%22&type=); also `underflow`); there are many results matching it, all seemingly unrelated (or perhaps I missed it).",
